Frontend Response Contract

The frontend renders from route and outcome. It must not infer state by parsing answer text. One contract shape is used for all routes; unused fields are null.

{
  "query\_id": "qry\_123",
  "correlation\_id": "corr\_123",
  "outcome": "answered | refused | clarification\_required | escalated | rejected",
  "route": "LLM | REFUSAL | CLARIFICATION | HUMAN\_REVIEW | SECURITY\_INCIDENT | REJECTED",
  "safety": {
    "risk\_level": "LOW | MEDIUM | HIGH | RESTRICTED",
    "policy\_state": "allowed | blocked | needs\_more\_context",
    "disclaimer\_required": false
  },
  "confidence\_state": "sufficient | limited | insufficient | conflicting\_sources | stale\_sources | restricted\_sources",
  "source\_bundle": {
    "source\_bundle\_id": "sb\_123",
    "retrieval\_method": "keyword\_mvp",
    "eligible\_source\_count": 4,
    "excluded\_source\_count": 2,
    "sources": []
  },
  "answer": {
    "text": "...",
    "citations": [],
    "limitations": []
  },
  "next\_action": null,
  "audit\_reference": {
    "audit\_chain\_id": "aud\_123"
  }
}

Security Correction

Do not expose latest\_event\_hash, previous\_event\_hash, event sequences, classifier internals, policy internals or raw audit material to the client. The frontend receives only the opaque audit\_chain\_id.
